\end{proof}


The system in Example \ref{ex-urbano} bears some similarities with the previous one although the dependence of $\tilde{\rho}_z({\cal{M}})$ with respect to $z$ appears to be much more complicated and we will only be able to describe it partially. 
We start our analysis by slightly improving our Theorem \ref{thm-algo-upperbound}.  This improvement will allow us to derive a better upper bound on $\tilde\rho({\cal{M}})$ than the one already obtained in Example~\ref{ex-urbano}. \begin{proposition}
For any arbitrary $\mu>0$, suppose that for every $z\in \mathbb{R}^2$ of norm 1 there exists a product $A_z\in {\cal{M}}^{t_z}$ for some $t_z\leq \bar t\in\mathbb{N}$ such that $|A_z z|^{1/t_z}\leq \mu,$ then,

